node.accessibility_caption:
In the Swiss Alps, a cow is airlifted by helicopter down the mountain ahead of the Urnerboden annual cow parade. 

Around 10 cows were taken down the mountain due to old age or injury, with approximately 990 others walking down. 

Farmer Jonas Arnold said: 'One reason for the helicopter transport is that you can't reach some pastures by car, and the other is that some cows are injured, so they don't have to walk all the way down. I didn't ask a cow how it feels after such a flight as it couldn't answer, but it's only a short distance and it has to keep going.' 

#cow #animals #environment #mountain #switzerland 

REUTERS/Arnd Wiegmann
